name: Carson Beck
summary: Georgia's quarterback, Carson Beck, sustained a shoulder injury during the SEC championship game against Texas and was forced to leave the game. Backup quarterback Gunner Stockton took over in the second half, but Beck later returned for one final play in overtime. Beck's return was crucial as he handed off the ball to running back Daijun Edwards, who scored the winning touchdown. Beck's injury is expected to be further evaluated with an MRI, and the team will await the results to determine the extent of his injury.

name: Pearl Harbor day
summary: On December 7th, various organizations and government entities commemorated the 83rd anniversary of the Pearl Harbor attack. Governor Newsom proclaimed December 7, 2024, as Pearl Harbor Remembrance Day, while the Pacific Command held a ceremony to honor the past and pass on the legacy to young service members. Hawaii News Now reported on the ceremony marking the anniversary, and the Department of Defense and LiveNOW from FOX paid tribute to the victims and survivors. Executive Office of the Governor Ron DeSantis issued a memorandum to fly flags at half-staff in honor of the day. USA TODAY presented photos of the attack, while EL PAÍS USA provided a timeline of the events leading to the United States' entry into World War II. Finally, NC.gov announced that both U.S. and North Carolina flags would be flown at half-staff to honor National Pearl Harbor Remembrance Day.

name: Timothee Chalamet
summary: Acclaimed actor Timothée Chalamet has emerged as a surprising college football enthusiast, making his debut as a guest picker on ESPN's popular pregame show "College GameDay." Chalamet's appearance has generated intrigue due to his unusual background as an actor rather than a football expert. Despite this, he impressed viewers with his knowledge of the upcoming championship matchup between Texas and Georgia. Chalamet's prediction for an Ohio team's victory on "GameDay" further showcased his understanding of college football. His involvement in the show highlights the growing popularity of the sport and the diverse backgrounds of its fans.

name: MLS
summary: The MLS Cup, the championship game of Major League Soccer, will be streamed for free on Apple TV this Saturday. Inter Miami CF captain Lionel Messi has been named the 2024 Landon Donovan MLS Most Valuable Player. The 2024 MLS Best XI has been announced, with Messi and his Inter Miami teammate Jordi Alba being named to the team. Legendary LA rapper Warren G will perform at the 2024 MLS Cup, which will be held at the LA Galaxy's stadium. The game will also be available to watch on TV and through other streaming services. The MLS is considering shifting its calendar to accommodate a more crowded schedule. Messi has won the MLS MVP award, adding to his long list of honors.

name: Phil Robertson
summary: Phil Robertson, patriarch of the hit reality show "Duck Dynasty," has been diagnosed with Alzheimer's. The news was shared by Robertson's family on his podcast, Unashamed, revealing that the 78-year-old has been battling the incurable disease. Robertson's family, including his wife Kay and sons Willie, Jase, and Jep, expressed their love and support for him during this difficult time, highlighting his strong faith and unwavering spirit.

name: Liverpool
summary: In the 2024/2025 Premier League season, Liverpool FC has faced exciting matches, including a thrilling 3-3 draw with Newcastle and a dominant 2-0 victory over Manchester City. NBC Sports highlighted key takeaways from the Liverpool vs. Manchester City game. Amidst contract negotiations, star player Mohamed Salah has expressed a willingness to extend his stay at Liverpool for a year, while The Athletic reported on his frustration with the club's handling of talks. Unfortunately, Liverpool's clash with Everton was postponed due to Storm Darragh, as reported by The Associated Press and NBC Sports. Despite the setback, Liverpool has reached an agreement with Salah on a two-year contract extension, as confirmed by The Mirror and Sports Illustrated.

name: Paul Mescal
summary: Paul Mescal, known for his charming appearance, hosted Saturday Night Live (SNL) on December 7th, 2024. Despite his charisma, critics noted that the show's sketches suffered from poor writing, diminishing his impact. However, Mescal's GQ recognition as the "Most Stylish Person of 2024" and his daring fashion choices in SNL, including short shorts, garnered attention. In a musical sketch, Mescal showcased his singing abilities in a parody of "Gladiator II." Despite the show's shortcomings, Mescal's enthusiasm and willingness to embrace the challenge were evident, with a highlight being the return of the beloved "Church Lady" character. Additionally, the promotion for the episode featured a humorous reference to Mescal's resemblance to the fictional gladiator Maximus. While one reviewer found the upcoming film "Gladiator II" to be lacking in Oscar potential, others suggested it still warranted a visit to the cinema.
